 * A Random Choice of further projects for the experienced constructor:-
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------

   Audio Harmonic Distortion Meter/SINAD Meter.

   Multimeter. PROBABLY IMPOSSIBLE.

   RF Voltmeter. THIS WILL BE VERY DIFFICULT TO CALIBRATE, (The RF Probe
   is already built).

   AC Milli-Voltmeter. 10Hz TO 1MHz, 10mV OR BETTER SENSITIVITY.

   RF Spectrum Analyser, (or Panoramic Adapter). 100KHz TO 1.5GHz OR MORE,
   BANDWIDTH DOWN TO 2.5KHZ, THIS WILL BE VERY, VERY DIFFICULT.

   Games Port Multimeter. PROBABLY IMPOSSIBLE, (This is under developement
   and WILL be a NON ISOLATED ~Bench Multitester~).

   Synthesised RF Signal Generator. WILL BE FOR THE AMATEUR BANDS ONLY.

   Modulation Meter. FM/AM, FM MODE WILL BE HARD.

   Marker Oscillator. PROBABLY 455KHz, 1MHz, 10MHz, 10.7MHz, 21.4MHz
   AND OTHERS.

   Single Channel Data Logger. HARDWARE BUILT, SOFTWARE NEAR COMPLETION.

   Thermometer. FOR SCIENTIFIC MEASUREMENTS.

   Pressure Sensor. SUBJECT TO AVAILABILITY OF SUITABLE TRANSDUCER.

   Light Meter. FOR PHOTOGRAPHERS.

   Audio Spectrum Analyser. 100Hz TO 12KHz, 512 POINT FFT,
   THIRD PARTY SOFTWARE AVAILABLE, HARDWARE UNDER CONSTRUCTION.

   Revolution Counter. FOR HIGH ROTATIONAL SPEEDS.

   Etc... etc... etc...

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

  These projects take a considerable amount of time to develop and build but
  I will eventually get there in the end. If anyone has any ideas for other
  testgear projects then let me know via Email, see below. Calibrated
  versions of a Project? will be for the AMIGA A1200, although they will
  work on the A500, A500(+) and A600 also but NOT calibrated.

